HEADWORD: Graylag
<hw>Gray"lag`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The common wild gray goose (<spn>Anser anser</spn>) of Europe,
believed to be the wild form of the domestic goose. See <it>Illust</it>.
of <er>Goose</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

